DonutDB takes the security of their services seriously. If you believe you have found a security vulnerability on our website, **do not** create a public issue. Instead, please report it privately.

{{Alert info|title=Warning!|text=Do not create a public issue report or share the vulnerability with any other party.}}

If you discover a security vulnerability on DonutDB, please report it through one of these channels:

{{Table
| 1/1=Email
| "1/2=business.nmc [at] outlook [dot] com"

| 2/1=Discord (DM)
| "2/2=@numenmc"

| 3/1=Discord (Guild) (Preferred)
| 3/2=Please join our [[https://discord.donutdb.net|Discord]] and create a ticket
}}

Please leave as much detail as possible to help us reproduce and investigate the issue. We aim to respond within 48 hours of reporting.

== Information to include ==
Please include this information with your security advisory:
{{List unordered
| 0=Description of the issue
| 1=Steps to reproduce
| 2=Affected endpoints, pages, or features
| 3=Relevant screenshots, logs, outputs, or payloads
| 4=Your contact information, preferably for Discord
}}

== Scope ==
The following is **out of scope** for reporting:
{{List unordered
| 0=Third-party services out of our control
| 1=Social engineering attacks
| 2=Physical security
| 3=Denial-of-service (DoS/DDoS) attacks
}}

== Responsible disclosure expectations ==
We request that you:
{{List unordered
| 0=Do not publicly disclose the vulnerability until it has been addressed
| 1=Avoid accessing, modifying, or deleting user data beyond what is necessary to demonstrate the vulnerability
| 2=Do not perform actions that could degrade service availability or user experience
}}

We will not pursue legal action against individuals who report vulnerabilities in good faith, follow the disclosure policy, and who avoid privacy violations, data destruction, or service disruption.

== Response process ==
Upon receiving a report, we will:
{{List unordered
| 0=Acknowledge the report within 48 hours
| 1=Investigate and validate the issue
| 2=Patch the vulnerability if confirmed
| 3=Provide the reporter with updates
| 4=Notify the reporter when the issue is resolved
| 5=Publish a public notice regarding the patched vulnerability
}}
